name: Kaos
summary: The highly anticipated Netflix series "Kaos" has garnered mixed reviews. The Guardian praises it as a "furiously fun" and "masterpiece" drama about the Greek gods, while TIME commends its clever updates to Greek mythology. However, other reviews are less enthusiastic. Slant Magazine finds the series lacking an epic feel, while IGN criticizes Jeff Goldblum's portrayal of Zeus. The Observer gives a more positive assessment, commending the series for making good on Greek mythology. Variety, on the other hand, calls "Kaos" a "meandering mythological bore." Despite the differing opinions, there seems to be general agreement that Jeff Goldblum is a standout performer in the series.
